HEADWORD: Bipartient
<hw>Bi*par"tient</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>bis</ets> twice + <ets>partiens</ets>, <pos>p. pr.</pos> of
<ets>partire</ets> to divide.]</ety> <def>Dividing into two parts.</def>
-- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A number that divides another into two equal
parts without a remainder.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

